      {
        "id": 2000869,
        "name": "Gene Ferrara",
        "username": "Gene_Ferrara",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/77aa72/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2016-08-28T14:56:04.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>My note from 3/30/16:</p>\n<p>I agree its for someone who likes this style.  Its also a product of a the vintage.</p>\n<p>At first sip, fresh, red pomegranate juice with a spicy core and a hint of licorice and a mild cedar, tobacco leaf.</p>\n<p>With more time, more spice and tobacco,mint and other ripe and leafy flavors.  Not funky or green at all, building intensity after an hour or so.</p>\n<p>No harsh acids or tannins, delicious.</p>",
